&gt; _&quot;... I wanted the break to change to return back to biography and calculator choice ... I dont know what statements do I use to make it work ...&quot;_

Use a _loop_.

- _[The for Statement (The Java&amp;trade; Tutorials &amp;gt; Learning the Java Language &amp;gt; Language Basics)](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/for.html)_
- _[The while and do-while Statements (The Java&amp;trade; Tutorials &amp;gt; Learning the Java Language &amp;gt; Language Basics)](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/while.html)_

A lot of the _&quot;bugs&quot;_ in your code stem from the use of the _[Scanner#next](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/20/docs/api/java.base/java/util/Scanner.html#next())_ methods versus _[nextLine](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/20/docs/api/java.base/java/util/Scanner.html#nextLine())_.

The _next_ methods are useful for capturing multiple values within a single line, and not the entire line itself.

Here is a re-factor, where I&#39;m using a _[LinkedHashMap](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/20/docs/api/java.base/java/util/LinkedHashMap.html)_ to contain the questions and answers for the _biography_ option.

